    <h3 id="table elements">Making a table</h3>
    <ul>
      
        <li>thead - semantic</li>
        <li>tbody-semantic</li>
        <li>tfoot- semantic</li>
        <li>th-header of column</li>
        <li>tr- new table row</li>
        <li>td - new table data item</li>
        <li>rowspan ="x"- where x is number of rows</li>
        <li>colspan = "x" - where x is number of columns</li>
        </tr>
        
    </ul>
    <h3 id="CSS selectors"> CSS Selectors</h3>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>CSS Command</th>
            <th>Meaning</th>
        
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>*</td>
            <td> applies to all</td>
            <td></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>#id-name</td>
            <td> applies to ID's within html</td>
            <td></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>.class-name</td>
            <td> applies to classes within html</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    <h3 id="css positions">CSS Positions</h3>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Command</th>
            <th>Meaning</th>
            <th> Specificity </th>
            <th>notes/questions?</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>z-index</td>
            <td>which item is in front or back</td>
            <td>integers. highest value is foreground</td>
            <td> must position be absolute?</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td rowspan="4">position</td>
            <td>fixed</td>
            <td> stays on specific spot, regardless of scrolling</td>
            <td>like a navigation bar</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>absolute</td>
            <td>positions relative to closest parent (in absolute or relative), out of document flow.</td>
            <td> use top/left/bottom/right</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>relative</td>
            <td>use offset properties to change position relative to where it would naturally be</td>
            <td> will be static if no offset properties added</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>sticky</td>
            <td>scrolls into view, and then stops when it meets its offset</td>
            <td> similar to fixed but originally appears in flow of document</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td rowspan="3" border="solid">display</td>
            <td>block</td>
            <td> takes full width of container</td>
            <td>can adjust height and width</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>inline</td>
            <td>take up as little space as possible</td>
            <td>no adjustment of height/width</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>inline-block</td>
            <td> can be next to each other</td>
            <td>can be adjusted height/width</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>float</td>
            <td>moves an element to the right or left within its parent element</td>
            <td>must specific left or right</td>
            <td>specify width? or else it will be at the very edge?</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>clear</td>
            <td>how an element behaves when it bumps into another with the same parent</td>
            <td>left/right/both/none.Specifies which direction of that element should be clear of others</td>
            <td>often used with float</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    <h3  id="css box model">CSS Box Model</h3>
    <table >
        <tr>
            <th>Command</th>
            <th>Meaning</th>
            <th> Specificity </th>
            <th>notes/questions?</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td rowspan="2"><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/box-sizing">box-sizing</a></td>
            <td>content-box</td>
            <td colspan="2">renders width within parent without accounting for padding and border</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>border-box</td>
            <td colspan="2"> renders width within parent element with borders and padding</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
           <td>visibility:hidden</td> 
           <td>hides element from view on html without having to delete it from program </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td rowspan="2">margin</td>
            <td rowspan="2">can specify margin around box</td>
            <td>#px</td>
            <td>pixels around element. don't forget about vertical margin collapse</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>auto</td>
            <td>horizontally center obhect</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td rowspan="3">overflow</td>
            <td>visible</td>
            <td>default, content takes up extra space</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>hidden</td>
            <td>its hidden</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>scroll</td>
            <td>scroll bars within individual container</td>
        </tr>
    <tfoot>
        <tr>
            <td colspan="4">min-width, min-height, max-width, max-height</td>
        </tr>
    </tfoot>
    </table> 
    <h3 id="CSS colors"><a href="https://htmlcolorcodes.com/"> CSS Colors</a></h3>
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Hexadecimal</th>
                <th>RGB</th>
                <th>HSL</th>
                <th>alpha</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>#</td>
                <td>rgb()</td>
                <td>hsl()</td>
                <td>rgba() or hsla()</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>6 characters 0-9 and A-F</td> 
                <td> 3 values between 0 and 255</td>
                <td> 3 values, 1st is hue (0-360), and then percentages for saturation and lightness</td>
                <td>transparent =0.0 and opaque =1.0</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
    <h3 id="vscode shortcuts"> VSCode Shortcuts</h3>
<ul>
    <li>shift+alt+down arrow = repeat last action</li>
    <li> enter after / to close open elements </li>
</ul>
<h3 id="command central">Navigating Command Line</h3>
<ul>
    <li>pwd - print working directory</li>
    <li>mkdir - make a new folder</li>
    <li>ls - list all files in current folder</li>
    <li>cd - change directory</li>
    <li> use ".." to move to higher directory</li>
    <li> touch - make a file in current directory</li>
</ul>
